,Recommended,225300,12896175,"Posted: 11 November, 2014",all,NemesisLeon,"Absolutely brilliant level design.  That's what this game is about.  Story is alright but don't expect it to be in-your-face drama 24/7.  This is a game about fantastic atmosphere and you exploring the level.  Figuring out that one specific solution or finding that one specific item bring such a fantastic epiphany feeling when it happens.  This game is full of that.If you want stat grinding, a soap opera story, or a heavy combat focus, this isn't it.  If you want amazing level and puzzle design with matching quality atmosphere then you need to play this.The only possible downside is the usual adventure game trope of not knowing where to go occasionally.  Just go over the known areas you've been and keep searching, it doesn't take forever to find the way through."
