,Recommended,225300,10731578,"Posted: 23 June, 2014",all,Arakanga.Ra,"Many people complain that this game's controls suck and that it's so old it looks ugly. While the graphics aren't as good as the current games (obviously!) and some people might not be able to overcome this, I can't agree with the controls complaints. You need to understand that this game came out in 1997 when the current WSAD system wasn't the standard. Sure, it takes time to get used to the controls, but when you do, you will find out this is one of the most precise control systems.Now, finally to the review. I have very fond memories of this game and consider it one of the top games in Tomb Raider franchise. Great choice of locations (China, Venice, wreck of Maria Doria, Tibet), thick atmosphere and simple, but sufficient story...yes, there aren't as many movement options as in its successor, Tomb Raider III, but I never thought that matters. The only downside to this great game is the Steam port - what the flip is the problem with FMVs? They're all windowed and in small resolution. But other than that, this game is brilliant. If you aren't an impatient kind of gamer who hates games that really take some effort to finish, get it. It's classic and fun even today."
