76561198087786691,Recommended,225300,30094704,Posted: 21 February,all,Tirah,"First off, keep in mind that this game is 19 years old and will require some minor tweaking if you want it to look at least semi-decent. I absolutely don't recommend playing it as is, it looks really bad. Download and install the widescreen patch(http://tombraiders.net/stella/downloads/widescreen.html)first, then download this patch if the game displays a Windows border in fullscreen mode(http://community.pcgamingwiki.com/files/file/82-tomb-raider-series-fullscreen-border-fix/). The cutscenes are interlaced and look awful, but I remember them looking just as bad back in 1997.Now you're all set to play what many consider to be the best Tomb Raider game ever made. Compared to its predecessor, Tomb Raider 2 is much more action oriented. Personally I always liked this game more than the original, even if the combat is still the same lackluster ""run around like a headless chicken while holding the Fire button"" kind of thing. Other than being combat heavy, it's your standard classic Tomb Raider. Puzzles, platforming, deadly traps, mysterious artifacts, it's all there.Even after all these years, TR2 still has a charm that cannot be matched. There's something about its low poly enemies and silence only occasionally interrupted by bursts of music that makes this game scarier than the latest photorealistic reboot.I'm probably biased since this is a game I've completed many, many times since the 90's and I consider it to be the best game in the entire Tomb Raider franchise, but to me everything about it is perfect. Its controls are outdated but solid and you get used to them quickly. The sound design is amazing, the atmosphere creepy. The levels are huge with lots of nooks and cranies to explore and secrets to discover.Even if you're not an old Tomb Raider fan and you've only just discovered the franchise, do yourself a favor and play this game to see how the legend started.Oh, and whatever you do, do NOT press F12 while playing. It'll force the game into windowed mode and cutscenes will stop working. You'll then have to quit the game, go back to Steam and change the game settings back to fullscreen."
