,Recommended,225300,29503641,Posted: 26 January,all,eS,"OF COURSE I locked the butler inside the walk-in freezer. Who hasn't?! Now that we've dealt with that, let's see what we have here.Let me get this over with quickly and painlessly:- yes, the graphics and animations and whatnot are VERY dated and don't play along well with modern resolutions. The game, however, runs well enough for me, and that's all I care about (but I'm very forgiving in terms of gfx and resolution).- the platforming and puzzles are awesome and in my opinion, that's what the game is about. This game is pretty slow and methodic and if you want to find all the secrets, items, and explore every nook and cranny in general, then this is your cup of tea. The environments are varied, the gameplay never gets stale although some levels (like the motherfreakin' sunken ship) drag on for a bit too long.- the combat, however, is A-T-R-O-C-I-O-U-S. Whoever thought this game needed shooting should jump into a spike pit, seriously, I canNOT stress enough how clunky, unfair, cheap and absolutely unnecessary this aspect is. Let me give you an example. You can take around 10 shots before you drop dead. The bad guys in the later levels need 2 to 3 GRENADE SHOTS. Let that sink in. I don't care if it's ""just a game"", no videogame iteration of a human grunt-type enemy should be able to withstand three grenades to the noggin.That said, for me, the platforming outweighs the terrible combat just enough to get a ""Recommend"" from me. Oh, and definitely get during a sale, not worth full price at any rate.TL;DR version: graphics/presentation meh, platforming/puzzles BIG thumbs up, combat: NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!"
