,Not Recommended,225300,12615865,"Posted: 24 October, 2014",all,OmniMoron,"TLDR: The neverending story of backtracking, dying in blind platforming sections, opening doors with levers located miles away and tanking bullets in a hellish savefest. This game is not exatly how I remembered it to be.I had good memories of this game when it was released originally. Unfortunately they were far from the truth.It must have been just the horny teenager me drooling over Lara Crofts low polygon curves and hearing her moan while she climbs stuff. And I did stop back then like at the Venice levels or so, cause the jumping got on my nerves then too.There's nothing else in this game than visually cool looking places (which are kinda crappy looking nowadays) and some later single enemies to keep you interested in it.The plot is ridiculous, but let's get over it and see what we have left.You collect white, yellow and green phallus statues(?) as a hobby while doing your ridiculous quest of killing hundreds of hired guns and endangered animals that spawn from thin air.Enemies are harmless, only the flamethrower and snowmobile guys can kill you early on/middle game. That is IF you don't mess up your camera controls and lose sight of you and your enemies. You take bullets like a tank, but if you get set on fire or a snowmobile runs over your toes, you die instantly. Also as you would expect crows do more damage that bullets.Doors in this world are operated not by door handles, but huge levers located on the other side of the city.Controls are ok for the most part, but it's really hard to get used to the quirks like the player not jumping immidiately. Wall/object clipping is horrible in some places and ruins jumps and makes diving a pain in the rocky parts.You don't really aim your guns, Lara does it for you while you're jumping backflips. I really liked that feature when I played the game first time and still think it's really cool.The graphics ok for a game this old and some of the places are visually really good looking. But the graphics are generally REALLY unclear and make finding what ever you're searching very hard. Simple things like ledges are hidden in the textures which are not seamless at all.Lara's animations look great, but the basic thug animations look really poor. Their walking animation is like Minecraft Alpha poor.Enemies AI is crap too. Enemies also spawn to areas you have already cleared behind you (with no entrances).Videos didn't play ok on my computer, they played fullscreen interlaced with what ever program I had open on background showing through the video.Sounds are really crappy. Music was ok and some even good, but there was little of it.-The player animations take FOREVER, are not cancelable and you have to repeat them in order to progress in the game. Even death animations have to wait for the previous to complete.(This makes 30% of the play time)-The game relies on the player having to return to visited parts of the map constantly.(This makes 350%-1050% of the play time)-Some platformer sections are a pain and require you to know where to jump beforehand blindly.(This makes 20% of the play time and forces you to save every 3 seconds)I liked the puzzle solving (including the drag boxes type) parts, but they are the easy part and not a match to the annoyance of always searching the right kind of blurry texture for a way to go or knowing that you'll have to backtrack again to progress.The game takes a long time to complete. But it's not cause there's so much content, only because you have to backtrack 10 times (I'm not even exaggerating) every map and wait for the animations to complete.I ment to complete this game now for the 14 year old me, but it was so unbelievably painful that I had to stop right at the end before I gRJAF_AgatgrlagricASTKgu"
