76561198299857110,Recommended,225300,24487617,"Posted: 23 July, 2016",all,KitsunetheShujinko45,"This game is my CHILDHOOD!! This game is definitely one of the best games on the Playstation, alongside the first game. Since it has been a long time since I've ever played it (on PC), I had to get used to the controls and they got a little hard to get used to, but if you use a controller, then it's a BLAST! I do have some cons, but it's on the list below,~~~PROS~~~-Great level design-An outstanding soundtrack that fits Lara Croft-Interesting Puzzles-Great improvement from having cheap weapons (in the 1st) to having multiple weapons that are usable for most occasions, (Like using the Harpoon Gun underwater, which is a pretty impressive Improvement if you ask me.)-Flares (First Tomb Raider to have Flares)-The compass is replaced with a Status thing? (Really, That compass from the 1st game was absolutely useless.)-More cutscenes (Instead of having a cutscene at the end of the last level in the specific area.)-Most classic ending scene. (Everyone knows what I mean.)~~~CONS~~~-A kinda cliche story (The bad guy scares you then doesn't really appear until the end.)-This game has the least amount of bosses! (A total of 6! It's 4 if you don't count the T-Rex's that contain the Gold Dragon in the first level. And I did count the Double Pistol goonies in Opera House and Home Sweet Home.)-You can't change Screen Resolution (In the PC port.)-The only hard boss was the final boss, (""Whoever"" the Dragon.)-The classic 'I STEAL YOUR WEAPONS ♥♥♥♥♥!!' level. (Luckily, you keep your ammo, flares, and Health packs for some reason...)-Water Levels (Use that Harpoon Gun to your advantage, PLEASE!!)-Nude Code's existence (I love Core & Eidos adding that hilarious code, Every fan knows what I'm talking about.)-Hair Logic (Lara's hair flies all over the place e.e)-Stone Warriors Spear ones. (I hate these damn enemies so much... they are the killer of my nightmares.)This is the end of my review, I would definitely start the Series with this game if you're new to it. Rating would be... 8.5/10."
